Comment.Text: If the ship is not within RangeThreshold then play the landingarea+align animation (waving both arms up and down in front of their body)

* Get the ship's position relative to the assigned landing pad* Set the Height threshold (Currently set to be plus and minus 1 from the Target Height)* Set the Negative Offset threshold (The positive threshold is already determined by the input variable)* Set the Angle threshold the ship is guided towards (angle threshold is used for both yaw and roll)"Thresholds" are the areas in space (between min and max values) that the ship is guided towards.The Origin of the thresholds are the assigned Landing Pad's Origin, plus the Target Height.
Take the Target Height then subtract and add 1 to its value to create a target min and target max threshold that the ship is guided towards.
Get the ship's position relative to the landing pad

Take the OffsetThreshold input, then apply the same negative value to the NegativeOffset variable. This combined with the positive offset variable gives a threshold window that the ship is guided towards.This threshold is used for the ship's horizontal plane positioning

Take the AngleThreshold input, then apply the same negative value to the NegativeAngle variable. This combined with the positive offset variable gives a threshold window that the ship is guided towards.
If the ship is within all other thresholds then tell the ship to decend to land
